name: AnnotationFormatError
comment:
Thrown when the annotation parser attempts to read an annotation
 from a class file and determines that the annotation is malformed.
 This error can be thrown by the {@linkplain
 java.lang.reflect.AnnotatedElement API used to read annotations
 reflectively}.

constructors.name: AnnotationFormatError
constructors.comment:
Constructs a new <tt>AnnotationFormatError</tt> with the specified
 detail message.

constructors.name: AnnotationFormatError
constructors.comment: Constructs a new AnnotationFormatError with the specified detail message and cause. Note that the detail message associated with cause is not automatically incorporated in this error's detail message.

constructors.name: AnnotationFormatError
constructors.comment:
Constructs a new <tt>AnnotationFormatError</tt> with the specified
 cause and a detail message of
 <tt>(cause == null ? null : cause.toString())</tt> (which
 typically contains the class and detail message of <tt>cause</tt>).
